<paragraph id="8BBC36C6FFE4FF8DFEB1FAA5FECB5156" blockId="17.[191,1442,1256,1923]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">
<collectingCountry id="F3147656FFE4FF8DFEB1FAA5FE6F5243" box="[256,418,1292,1318]" name="Argentina" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">ARGENTINA</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFE4FF8DFE1EFAA4FDB35243" box="[431,638,1292,1319]" country="Argentina" name="La Rioja" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">La Rioja Province</collectingRegion>
, Chilecito, El Portezuela Municipal Park; 
<date id="FFBD1006FFE4FF8DFBD3FAA5FAFC5243" box="[1122,1329,1292,1318]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" value="2020-11-06">6 November 2020</date>
, 2024; N. Greefpool. Host: 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFE4FF8DFE37FA86FCE7522D" authority="Mello-Leitao" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1941" box="[390,810,1326,1352]" class="Arachnida" family="Xenoctenidae" genus="Xenoctenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marmoratus">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFE4FF8DFE37FA86FD59522D" box="[390,660,1327,1352]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Xenoctenus marmoratus</emphasis>
Mello-Leitão
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFE4FF8DFC8BFA87FC17522C" authorityName="Ramirez &amp; Silva-Davila" authorityYear="2017" box="[826,986,1326,1353]" class="Arachnida" family="Xenoctenidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Xenoctenidae</taxonomicName>
), adult male [det. N. Ferretti, 
<collectionCode id="ED12AE03FFE4FF8DFA9EFA87FEF4520C" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">CERZOS- CONICET</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode id="ED12AE03FFE4FF8DFEF2FAE6FEB1520C" box="[323,380,1359,1385]" country="Viet Nam" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/0nv9-p2k7" name="University of Science, Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">UNS</collectionCode>
, Bahia Blanca, AR; D. Fernanda Silva Davila, 
<collectionCode id="ED12AE03FFE4FF8DFCC7FAE6FC2C520C" box="[886,993,1359,1385]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">UNMSM</collectionCode>
, Lima, PE], 
<quantity id="4CFB9B23FFE4FF8DFBD6FAE6FB7B520F" box="[1127,1206,1359,1386]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" unit="mm" value="14.0">14 mm</quantity>
long (wasp, 
<quantity id="4CFB9B23FFE4FF8DFAF0FAE6FA59520F" box="[1345,1428,1359,1386]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" unit="mm" value="14.0">14 mm</quantity>
). The wasp grasped the spider’s right pedipalp near the end with her mandibles and dragged it backwards, dorsal side upward, across the outer concrete sidewalk of the park. She then pulled it across cobbled rock into a hole at the base of a low retaining wall (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFE4FF8DFD96FA1DFD2B52AB" author="Greefpool N." box="[551,742,1460,1486]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" refId="ref23713" refString="Greefpool N. 2020 a. Genus Tachypompilus. Available at http: // www. inaturalist. org / observations / 64324930. (Last accessed 11 November 2020)." type="url" year="2020">Greefpool 2020a</bibRefCitation>
; Greefpool, Chilecito, La Roija, AR, pers. comm. 2020). 
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFE4FF8DFAE9FA1DFE9D5294" author="Greefpool N." pageId="17" pageNumber="16" refId="ref23745" refString="Greefpool N. 2020 b. Genus Tachypompilus. Available at http: // www. inaturalist. org / observations / 64821463. (Last accessed 14 November 2020)." type="url" year="2020">Greefpool (2020b)</bibRefCitation>
photographed this wasp or another female without prey at the same location on 
<date id="FFBD1006FFE4FF8DFB79FA7FFA515295" box="[1224,1436,1494,1520]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" value="2020-11-13">13 November 2020</date>
, 2034 hours, searching for openings (presumably a nesting site) in the retaining wall (Greefpool pers. comm. 2020).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36C6FFE4FF8DFEB1F992FAAD51FD" blockId="17.[191,1442,1256,1923]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">
<materialsCitation id="3B6B3C9BFFE4FF8DFEB1F992FB415130" box="[256,1164,1594,1621]" collectingDate="2004-12-31" collectionCode="CET" country="Bolivia" location="Santa Cruz Department" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Santa Cruz">
<collectingCountry id="F3147656FFE4FF8DFEB1F992FEBC5130" box="[256,369,1595,1621]" name="Bolivia" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">BOLIVIA</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFE4FF8DFECFF992FD5F5130" box="[382,658,1595,1621]" country="Bolivia" name="Santa Cruz" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Santa Cruz Department</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFE4FF8DFD11F992FCEC5130" box="[672,801,1595,1621]" country="Bolivia" name="Santa Cruz" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Santa Cruz</collectingRegion>
; 
<date id="FFBD1006FFE4FF8DFC9EF992FBC45130" box="[815,1033,1594,1621]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" value="2004-12-31">
<collectingDate id="EFF9E9EEFFE4FF8DFC9EF992FBC45130" box="[815,1033,1594,1621]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" value="2004-12-31">31 December 2004</collectingDate>
</date>
, 0956 
<collectionCode id="ED12AE03FFE4FF8DFBE6F992FB415130" box="[1111,1164,1595,1621]" country="Spain" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/3sv8-kt7s" name="Centro de Estudios Tropicales" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">CET</collectionCode>
</materialsCitation>
; 
<collectionCode id="ED12AE03FFE4FF8DFB2BF992FB715130" box="[1178,1212,1595,1621]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">J-P</collectionCode>
. Boerekamps. Host: 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFE4FF8DFF71F9F4FEFF5112" box="[192,306,1629,1655]" class="Arachnida" family="Ctenidae" genus="Ctenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFE4FF8DFF71F9F4FEC15112" box="[192,268,1629,1655]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Ctenus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, adult male. The wasp grasped the patella of the immobilized wandering spider’s left pedipalp with her mandibles and, maintaining it dorsal side upward, walked backwards on the substrate (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFE4FF8DFB37F9D7FA9951FD" author="Boerekamps J-P." box="[1158,1364,1662,1688]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" refId="ref21445" refString="Boerekamps J-P. 2004. Tribe Pompilini. Available at https: // www. inaturalist. org / observations / 69715438. (Last accessed 18 February 2021)." type="url" year="2004">Boerekamps 2004</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36C6FFE4FF8DFEB1F936FCA75198" blockId="17.[191,1442,1256,1923]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">
<collectingCountry id="F3147656FFE4FF8DFEB1F936FE5E51DC" box="[256,403,1695,1721]" name="Colombia" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">COLOMBIA</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFE4FF8DFE2CF936FD1B51DF" box="[413,726,1695,1722]" country="Colombia" name="Cundinamarca" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Cundinamarca Department</collectingRegion>
, Nocaima; 
<date id="FFBD1006FFE4FF8DFCE5F936FBD051DC" box="[852,1053,1695,1721]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" value="2020-11-08">8 November 2020</date>
; O. Encisoa. Host: 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFE4FF8DFB43F936FA6C51DF" box="[1266,1441,1695,1722]" class="Arachnida" family="Ctenidae" genus="Ancylometes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFE4FF8DFB43F936FAB651DC" box="[1266,1403,1695,1721]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Ancylometes</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFE4FF8DFF79F968FEFF51B9" box="[200,306,1729,1756]" class="Arachnida" family="Ctenidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Ctenidae</taxonomicName>
), adult or subadult female. The wasp examined the immobilized wandering spider with her antennae as it laid, dorsal side upward, on the ground (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFE4FF8DFD06F94BFC935198" author="Encisoa O." box="[695,862,1762,1789]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" refId="ref23013" refString="Encisoa O. 2020 a. Spider Wasps (Family Pompilidae). Available at https: // www. inaturalist. org / observations / 65434458. (Last accessed 23 November 2020)." type="url" year="2020">Encisoa 2020a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36C6FFE4FF8DFEB1F8ADFDCD50E6" blockId="17.[191,1442,1256,1923]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">
<materialsCitation id="3B6B3C9BFFE4FF8DFEB1F8ADFCB3507B" box="[256,894,1796,1823]" country="Colombia" location="Cundinamarca Department" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Cundinamarca">
<collectingCountry id="F3147656FFE4FF8DFEB1F8ADFE5E507B" box="[256,403,1796,1822]" name="Colombia" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">COLOMBIA</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFE4FF8DFE2CF8ADFD1B507A" box="[413,726,1796,1823]" country="Colombia" name="Cundinamarca" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Cundinamarca Department</collectingRegion>
, San Bernardo
</materialsCitation>
; 
<date id="FFBD1006FFE4FF8DFC38F8ADFBD6507B" box="[905,1051,1796,1823]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" value="2020-05-23">23 May 2020</date>
, 1544; O. Martinez. Host: Unidentified species (
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFE4FF8DFED0F88FFDC75024" authorityName="Bertkau" authorityYear="1878" box="[353,522,1830,1857]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Anyphaenidae</taxonomicName>
), adult or subadult female [det. A. Brescovit, S. C. Crews]. The wasp grasped the immobilized ghost spider near the end of its left pedipalp and dragged it, dorsal side upward, backwards across the ground (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFE4FF8DFEFAF8C0FE3950E6" author="Martinez O." box="[331,500,1897,1923]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" refId="ref25552" refString="Martinez O. 2020. Tachypompilus mendozae. Available at https: // www. inaturalist. org / observations / 47448253. (Last accessed 25 December 2020)." type="url" year="2020">Martinez 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36C6FFE7FF8EFEB1FF7FFB9C5630" blockId="18.[192,1441,214,341]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">
<collectingCountry id="F3147656FFE7FF8EFEB1FF7FFE855795" box="[256,328,214,240]" name="Peru" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">PERU</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFE7FF8EFEE0FF7FFE685795" box="[337,421,214,240]" country="Peru" name="Ancash" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Ancash</collectingRegion>
Department, Juipon (
<quantity id="4CFB9B23FFE7FF8EFD28FF7FFD235795" box="[665,750,214,240]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="18" pageNumber="17" unit="m" value="2600.0">2600 m</quantity>
elevation); 
<date id="FFBD1006FFE7FF8EFCC1FF7FFBF85794" box="[880,1077,214,241]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17" value="2015-02-24">24 February 2015</date>
; S. Dickson. Host: 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFE7FF8EFAB7FF7FFF2C5674" authorityName="Karsch" authorityYear="1880" class="Arachnida" family="Nemesiidae" genus="Acanthogonatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="18" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFE7FF8EFAB7FF7FFF2C5674" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Acanthogonatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
? 
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFE7FF8EFF40FF51FE815674" box="[241,332,248,273]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">incursus</emphasis>
(Chamberlin) (
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFE7FF8EFE4BFF5EFD505677" box="[506,669,247,274]" class="Arachnida" family="Pycnothelidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="18" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pycnothelidae</taxonomicName>
) [det. P. A. Goloboff, 
<collectionCode id="ED12AE03FFE7FF8EFC3DFF5EFBCB5674" box="[908,1030,247,273]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">CONICET</collectionCode>
. Buenos Aires, AR), subadult female. The wasp pulled the paralyzed pycnothelid spider, dorsal side upward, across the ground and up a vertical adobe wall and into a hole, grasping its left pedipalp with her mandibles (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFE7FF8EFC14FE93FB885630" author="Dickson S." box="[933,1093,314,341]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17" refId="ref22821" refString="Dickson S. 2015. Dando de comer a los animales de la chacra pelea Arana Vs Avispa. Available at https: // m. facebook. com / photo. php? fbid = 852064918168182 &amp; id = 100000940450435 &amp; set = a. 852063881501619. (Last accessed 25 January 2021)." type="url" year="2015">Dickson 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
